"use strict";(self.webpackChunkfrontend=self.webpackChunkfrontend||[]).push([[889],{6889:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"tableOfContents":["The Aspiration for a Better Work-Life Balance","The Concrete Advantages of Temporary Work in Healthcare","MediShift\xae: Your Ally for a Tailor-Made Career","Shape Your Ideal Career with MediShift\xae"],"content":[{"title":"The Aspiration for a Better Work-Life Balance: A Fundamental Trend","paragraphs":["Healthcare professionals, particularly pharmacists, are expressing a growing desire for greater control over their schedules, a better balance between professional and personal life, and varied work experiences.","It is documented that more than 40% of pharmacists work part-time in Switzerland. This is a definite advantage when one wants to combine family life and professional life. This trend is particularly marked among the younger generations who are seeking a better balance between these two spheres of their lives.","This evolution of professional expectations is not anecdotal but reflects a profound change in the way healthcare professionals view their careers and overall well-being."],"image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573497620053-ea5300f94f21?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80","imageCaption":"Healthcare professionals are seeking a better work-life balance"},{"title":"The Concrete Advantages of Temporary Work in Healthcare: More Than Just Flexibility","paragraphs":["Temporary work in the healthcare sector offers numerous advantages that go far beyond simple schedule flexibility:","\u2022 The freedom to choose when and where to work, allowing one to adapt their schedule to personal priorities","\u2022 The opportunity to gain experience in various pharmacy or healthcare facility environments, thus enriching one\'s professional journey","\u2022 The possibility of benefiting from potentially higher hourly rates for short-term assignments","\u2022 Avoiding long-term office dynamics if desired, reducing potential sources of relational stress","\u2022 An ideal solution for semi-retirees, those returning to the job market after a break, or those managing significant family responsibilities","The desire for flexibility is more than just a preference; it is a growing expectation, particularly among younger generations and female professionals, who make up 75% of pharmacists. Beyond remuneration, the non-monetary benefits of temporary work - the variety of assignments, skill enhancement, professional network development, and reduction of burnout risk - are powerful attraction factors."]},{"title":"MediShift\xae: Your Ally for a Tailor-Made Career","paragraphs":["MediShift\xae was designed as an empowerment tool for healthcare professionals, offering them the means to shape their careers on their own terms. The platform offers:","\u2022 A user-friendly interface to find and apply for temporary assignments that match your skills and availability","\u2022 Total transparency regarding assignment details (location, duration, requirements)","\u2022 Personalized support from the MediShift\xae team to accompany you on your professional journey","\u2022 Assurance of compliance with Swiss temporary work legislation, guaranteeing you security and protection","The platform emphasizes a user-centric approach, where your preferences and wishes are taken into account to offer you assignments that truly meet your expectations. Respect for legal provisions concerning working hours, rest periods, and night or Sunday work is fundamental to establishing a lasting relationship of trust."],"image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551836022-deb4988cc6c0?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80","imageCaption":"MediShift\xae allows healthcare professionals to regain control of their careers"},{"title":"Shape Your Ideal Career with MediShift\xae","paragraphs":["Temporary work via MediShift\xae represents a unique opportunity for healthcare professionals to redefine their relationship with work. By choosing when, where, and how you want to practice your profession, you regain control of your career and your life.","This flexible approach to work is not only beneficial for your personal balance, but it also helps to enrich your professional experience, expand your network, and develop new skills in various environments.","In a sector as demanding as healthcare, where burnout and professional exhaustion are real risks, the ability to manage one\'s time and workload becomes a valuable asset for a sustainable and fulfilling career.","MediShift\xae invites you to explore this new way of considering your professional journey, where flexibility rhymes with opportunity, and where balance is no longer a luxury but a right."]}],"keywords":["temporary pharmacist work Switzerland","flexible pharmacist French-speaking Switzerland","pharmacy assignment Geneva","MediShift benefits healthcare professionals","work-life balance"]}')}}]);